    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-10-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-10-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="86" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d86">
                <head>No. 86.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Low</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                        of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-10-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 4,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 101.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 172, under date of 12th
                            July last, relating to the departure of thirty Chinese youths for
                            education in the United States, and bespeaking my good offices in their
                            behalf at the request of Li Hung Chang, has been received. The arrival
                            of these young men is regarded with interest, and it will give me
                            pleasure to manifest my friendly feeling for them should a proper
                            occasion offer.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
